{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
[[Image:Charles Carnan Ridgely.jpg|thumb|right|Charles Carnan Ridgely]]

'''Charles Carnan Ridgely''' (December 6, 1760{{Ndash}} July 17, 1829) served as the  [[List of Governors of Maryland|15th]] [[Governor of Maryland|Governor]] of the state of [[Maryland]] in the [[United States]] from 1815 to 1818.  He also served in the [[Maryland House of Delegates]] from 1790 to 1795, and in the [[Maryland State Senate]] from 1796 to 1800.

His ancestral home, ''Hampton Mansion'' is now in the care of the [[National Park Service]] as [[Hampton National Historic Site]].

Ridgely's son John Carnan Ridgely (1790<U+2013>1867) married [[Eliza Ridgely]] (1803<U+2013>1867).

